  "text": "Whereas the preceeding module uses shape contours to refine and filter the position and pose of candidate pedestrians, the current pattern classification module utilizes the richer set of intensity features to make the distinction pedestrian versus non-pedestrian. The selection of the particular type of classifier was guided by the need to represent a complex decision boundary in high dimensional feature space with only a relatively small training set at the disposal, see Table 2 (negative samples consisted of the false positives of the cascade up to this point from previous bootstrapping steps [CITATION_1] ).",
